key_insights: Don't buy calls at the top of range - buy at bottom of range. Don't buy puts at bottom - buy puts at top of range
When 9 EMA crosses 21 EMA on 1 hour timeframe, take directional trade and ride it. Confirm on 15 min and 5 min charts
Stick with the same basket of stocks rather than constantly switching - you need to understand the characteristics and behavior of each stock
Don't trade stocks where buyers and sellers are balanced (supply/demand zones on top of each other) - want to see black open space for price to move
In a downtrend pattern (high, low, lower high, lower low), wait to buy calls at the pivot lows, not at current price
Watch the directional bias of the stock - don't fight the trend structure
Be patient and wait for price to come to your preferred entry zone rather than chasing
When VIX gets above 20, there is more volatility and price instability - be more cautious
Large wicks with whipsaw action back and forth is dangerous trading environment versus more candle body movement
Watch major tech stocks (Google, Apple, Microsoft, Nvidia) behavior when trading QQQ to confirm price action

notable_events: Regional bank earnings week of Oct 20 (Zions, HBT, Winchester, BOK, Capital One, East West Bank)
Regional bank credit scare Thursday causing selloff
Auto loan delinquencies and charge-offs (fraud concerns)
Average US car now $50k+ with 8-9% rates, $800+ monthly payments

summary: Bill Fanter provides a comprehensive weekly watchlist for October 20th, focusing on upcoming earnings (banks, Netflix, Tesla, autos), chart analysis of major indices and tech stocks, and emphasizes the importance of patience in trading - waiting for price to come to demand/supply zones rather than chasing. He stresses understanding stock behavior characteristics, respecting trend structure, and being cautious during high volatility periods with the VIX above 20.
